    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the Monte Carlo UQ ensemble demonstrates hemolysis predictions below the absolute clinical NIH threshold at the 97.5th percentile across all five operating points, and that the detailed narrative documentation of the hemolysis index validation campaign (morrison-cou2-hemolysis-index-absolute) was judged sufficient to establish confidence in the result. Credibility factor gaps are acknowledged and recorded as epistemic limitations to be addressed in the next design iteration. The decision to accept despite multiple factors below required levels reflects the low assurance level designation and the sponsor's acceptance of residual risk pending device-specific validation.",
